# .trivyignore
# BLUEPRINT: Composer 2 implements from this structure
# PURPOSE: Trivy CVE ignore list. Lists specific CVEs that are accepted risks,
#          cross-referenced with docs/security/accepted-risks.md for justification.
#          Per spec §26.12 item 380.
# FORMAT: One CVE ID per line. Comments (#) are supported.
# POLICY:
#   - Every entry MUST have a corresponding entry in docs/security/accepted-risks.md
#   - Every entry MUST have a review date; entries older than 90 days are re-evaluated
#   - Entries are removed when the vulnerability is patched or the package is replaced
# SECTIONS:
#   - Accepted CVEs with justification reference
# DESIGN DECISIONS:
#   - This file is intentionally sparse at template initialization
#   - During project lifecycle, CVEs are added here only after accepted-risks.md review
#   - No CVEs should be ignored without documented justification and review date

# Format:
# CVE-YYYY-XXXXX  # <package> - <reason> - reviewed: YYYY-MM-DD

# Example (remove in real projects; add real accepted CVEs):
# CVE-2024-00000  # example-package - no fix available; mitigated by network isolation - reviewed: 2025-01-01
